& [OriginArc] is why this project began
  + [origin_pressure] is the user wants a local-LLM coding-agent system that uses multiple models with distinct roles rather than one model prompted repeatedly
  + [origin_pressure] is the user wants four negotiated flowchart levels before code: application, subsystem, component, and code
  + [origin_pressure] is the user wants a strong Manager, medium Directors, lightweight Programmers, and a persistent Shaliach as protocol counsel and enforcement
  + [origin_pressure] is the user wants Specification-Justification-Solution and Data-Driven Design protocols to govern objectives, conditions, failures, forms, data subjects, transforms, and solution state
  + [origin_pressure] is the user wants the SOP framework incorporated in stages rather than discarded or paraphrased away
  + [origin_pressure] is the user has observed long Codex runs surviving through durable SOP attention and wants CodeLab to absorb that machinery
  + [citation_ref] is specifications/source/2026-05-29_hierarchical_agent_swarm_source.sop
  + [citation_ref] is coordination/framework_attention_load.sop

& [SpecificationArc] is how origin became architectural authority
  + [source_document] is specifications/source/2026-05-29_hierarchical_agent_swarm_source.sop
  + [canonical_working_specification] is specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  + [signature_state] is working_specification_unsigned
  + [authority_scope] is architecture, orchestration, model tiering, flowchart negotiation, implementation slicing, programmer review, and local model hosting
  + [primary_obligation] is preserve Shaliach, Manager, Director, and Programmer role distinctions
  + [primary_obligation] is negotiate all four flowchart layers before implementation unless explicitly waived by Manager
  + [primary_obligation] is use SJS and DataDrivenDesign ledgers when layer authority affects implementation
  + [narrative_gap] is governing specification is useful as active rail but remains unsigned under the SJS satisfaction-signature protocol

& [DecisionArc] is the major design choice sequence
  + [decision] is use Shaliach rather than Observer to avoid conflating CodeLab protocol counsel with the seven-faculty Observer
  + [decision] is use Manager for objective integrity, arbitration, layer approval, work slicing, and final review
  + [decision] is use Directors for medium-weight flowchart negotiation and perspective diversity
  + [decision] is use Programmers for bounded implementation slices after code-layer settlement
  + [decision] is support model diversity as a first-class goal instead of relying only on role prompts over one model
  + [decision] is prefer vLLM for NVIDIA/Linux throughput when environment is ready, while preserving Ollama and OpenAI-compatible routing
  + [decision] is preserve dry-run mode as a verification path independent of local LLM availability
  + [decision] is treat SOP as runtime substrate rather than background documentation
  + [citation_ref] is specifications/Hierarchical_Agent_Swarm.sop
  + [citation_ref] is coordination/framework_attention_load.sop

